            <h3>Treatment Sessions</h3>
            <p>Professional procedures in our state-of-the-art clinic with focus on comfort and safety.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">4</div>
            <h3>Aftercare & Follow-Up</h3>
            <p>Detailed aftercare instructions, skincare regimen, and regular follow-ups for optimal, lasting results.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="faq section bg-neutral-50">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="faq-grid">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Are cosmetic dermatology treatments safe for Indian skin?</h3>
            <p>Yes. Our dermatologists specialise in treating Indian skin types (Fitzpatrick IV-V). All treatments are customised to prevent hyperpigmentation and ensure safe, effective results.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>How do I choose the right cosmetic treatment?</h3>
            <p>During your free consultation, our dermatologist will assess your skin, discuss your goals, and recommend the most suitable treatments based on your skin type and concerns.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Is there any downtime after cosmetic procedures?</h3>
            <p>Most of our treatments have minimal to no downtime. Chemical peels may require 2-3 days, while laser treatments may need 3-5 days of recovery depending on the procedure.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>How much do cosmetic dermatology treatments cost?</h3>
            <p>Treatments start from Rs 1,500. Exact costs depend on the procedure, number of sessions, and treatment area. We provide detailed pricing during your free consultation.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Can I combine multiple cosmetic treatments?</h3>
            <p>Yes, combination therapies often give superior results. Your dermatologist will create a phased plan that safely combines treatments for maximum benefit.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>How long do results last?</h3>
            <p>Results vary by treatment. Laser and chemical peel results can last months to years with proper skincare. Maintenance sessions are recommended for sustained results.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

